 :tx/rationale "ASSESSMENT FINDING: Issue Inflation — 883 Total Issues as Second Project. 883 total issues (813 closed = 92%, 70 open = 8%). The 70 open issues span 8+ epics across 4 phases. While 92% closure rate appears healthy, the raw count creates management overhead. Sessions 036 and 028 spent significant time on administrative convergence — closing 136 tasks and 28 EPICs respectively — rather than implementation. This means issue management competes with productive work. The issue system designed to track work has become work itself. Three concerns: (1) 70 open issues across 4 phases means no single session can address them all — the backlog is permanently larger than one session can process. (2) Epic proliferation (19 open EPICs was reduced to a lower number but keeps growing) creates organizational hierarchy that costs attention. (3) The ratio of issues-created-per-session to issues-closed-per-session appears approximately 1:1, creating steady-state backlog rather than convergence to zero. FIX: Aggressive triage of the 70 open issues. Close or defer anything not on the critical path (Priorities 1-4 from this assessment). Target: < 20 open issues, < 5 open EPICs, all aligned with the 6-priority path. VERIFICATION: After triage, measure time-in-session spent on issue management vs implementation. Target: < 10% management overhead. INTERACTS WITH: Scope creep (issue creation is how scope expands), velocity stall (issue overhead may contribute), formalism cost risk (issue tracking is part of the formal overhead). TRACES TO: NEG-010 (issue management should close loops, not open them)."
